We use node-fetch@2 specifically — version 3 doesn't work with CommonJS require() on Windows without extra config.


"During testing I discovered the model was penalizing Fellows based on 
supervisor tone rather than actual behavior. For example, a Fellow who 
built a defect tracking system broken down by batch, machine and operator
 was scored 6 because the supervisor sounded unsatisfied — when the correct 
 score was 7. I fixed this by adding explicit bias detection rules to the prompt
  that separate supervisor tone from Fellow behavior evidence."

  This project is submitted as part of a recruitment assignment.
